</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2A3AFC5B77339E2C437533DCBD602CCB" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="FA4193431C130C75737C0F1E5C6EF95A" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2F065413E8BE533B33C9B7D87A9106D" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">
Turkey. 
<taxonomicName id="F73F555B5C9E35B822E2B0614C37A613" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" rank="kingdom">Plantae</taxonomicName>
Lyciae, ad fonts reginis 
<taxonomicName id="F6BA444C1BBAA773D520E6B180955573" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpinae">alpinae</taxonomicName>
montis Elmalu, 25 Jun 1860, 
<emphasis id="013B548AC58F0170E170714174819BB4" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">E. Bourgeau 271</emphasis>
(lectotype, 
<emphasis id="4B5B0266A2C8E1C4D7085DD1F4A7A0B5" bold="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">here designated</emphasis>
: G [G00330280 image!]; isolectotypes: G [G00380172 image!, p.p. central and right top two samples], G [G0038173 image!], K [K-000789856 image!]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AA092444FD2B4226B4744FFF1F402C0C" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F67E1FF4289E9BE026BAA364C02058ED" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4304117D0346E793FF3E30C2207388CD" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Armenia, Azerbaijan, Afghanistan, Georgia, Iran, Kyrgyz Republic, Pakistan, Turkey and Turkmenistan(?).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5FC14E75CB229C7E4C679C85ECBFDBCD" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" type="notes">
<paragraph id="CE7C53C6EDEA9BE3F9072786D54F2CC8" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="301B6EC5425C7335A142E697FB840F9A" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">
This taxon, accepted as 
<taxonomicName id="4429187F60D3BFB4A8063EC994FC2B5B" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa bellula" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis id="0AE41CE993CF5472AB6B7E0A8A84F9C6" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Eremopoa bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by several authors (see Names of Uncertain Application below), was first recognised infraspecifically by 
<bibRefCitation id="7B4066F44A0F3EAB5D6E6DC6F5BC64D8" author="Boissier, PE" editor="Boissier, PE" journalOrPublisher="5. H. Georg, Basilae" pageId="20" pageNumber="89" pagination="432 - 692" refId="B3" refString="Boissier, PE, 1884. Ordo CXLI. Gramineae. In: Boissier, PE, Ed., Flora Orientalis, vol. 5. H. Georg, Basilae: 432 - 692" title="Ordo CXLI. Gramineae." volumeTitle="Flora Orientalis, vol." year="1884">Boissier (1884)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="E29A4ACFA01154B896E64AC2A16302EC" authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1884" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa persica var. alpina" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="persica" variety="alpina">Poa persica var. alpina</taxonomicName>
. The variety is common in the highest elevations at which the genus occurs, in the alpine of Turkey, Iran and Afghanistan to the Pamir mountains, reaching 4000 m. Further study is needed to clarify the distinction of var. 
<taxonomicName id="D02149EE514365605DD7565D3C0D5195" authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1884" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. alpina" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="persica" variety="alpina">alpina</taxonomicName>
from var. 
<taxonomicName id="653278C6026C27241AE3DD600CD40112" authorityName="Asch &amp; Graebn" authorityYear="1900" baseAuthorityName="Trin." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. diaphora" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="persica" variety="diaphora">diaphora</taxonomicName>
and these from 
<taxonomicName id="175CE84090F9BBFFBD80FABCD97087DF" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa bellula" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis id="56460EDC1BAD241A38AB083B39E63443" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Eremopoa bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as the material placed here appears heterogenous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0FBDDF6E6240312FEB9079C1D0CBA443" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">
Of the six syntypes of var. 
<taxonomicName id="A88595531C5B2FAB75222B34453B93F6" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. alpina" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="bellula" variety="alpina">alpina</taxonomicName>
cited by Boissier (
<emphasis id="DD37959AE8CF10280A683AF980D14A4B" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Bourgeau 271</emphasis>
, hab. in alpinis, montes supra Elmali Lyciae [G00380172, G0038173, G00330280, K000789856]; 
<emphasis id="B45C6AC06A91E69F0C50E2961EC13B65" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Kotschy 12</emphasis>
, Tarus Cilicicus, 5
<normalizedToken id="C8A6F3A07A48CBF5DD3192474E9DD278" originalValue="–6000’">-6000'</normalizedToken>
; Prairies humides de la region alpine du Taurus, au Boulgarmden [as 
<emphasis id="3D87272D260F6345F046C20A13EF8A0E" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">12d</emphasis>
: G00330281, K000789851 image!]; 
<emphasis id="EF3634BD3E3C91910201A118373AF9BB" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Balansa s.n.</emphasis>
, Jul-Aug 1855 [K000789857, P02358251 p.p. bottom right]; 
<emphasis id="B1CABF1E2219120EE5A63B3FA70D5CD3" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Blanche s.n</emphasis>
., Libani cacuminal; 
<emphasis id="6CB13BA87386B0981AC31E9C79307A4C" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Kotschy 477</emphasis>
, mons Kuh Delu Persiae australis, 10 Jun 1842 [BM000959359 image!, E!, G00308632 image!, P02358251! p.p. &quot;fo. pygmaea&quot; bottom left]), we select 
<emphasis id="F2E6A7E32BC0ACCD7911BD08BDE4810C" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Bourgeau 271</emphasis>
as the lectotype as it is typical of the form. As noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="8CB49340B9F87BBD4DDD2A6A00DFC963" author="Samuelsson, G" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal of Botany" pageId="22" pageNumber="91" refId="B47" refString="Samuelsson, G, 1950. In: Rechinger KH (Ed.) Zur Flora von Cypren (Reliquiae Samuelssonianae II.). Arkiv foer Botanik, n.s.1(9): 417." title="In: Rechinger KH (Ed.) Zur Flora von Cypren (Reliquiae Samuelssonianae II.). Arkiv foer Botanik, n. s. 1 (9): 417." year="1950">Samuelsson (1950)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<emphasis id="B76AE8568FB85C2C297BE01395E685C7" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Sintenis</emphasis>
syntype (mons Troodos, Cypri) represents a separate form that is treated here as 
<taxonomicName id="1ED8DF2E38E831B993C31290AA8A781E" authorityName="H. Lindb., Arsbok-Vuosik. Soc. Sci. Fenn. 20 B (7): 5. 1942 (emend. Lindberg" authorityYear="1946" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa sintenisii" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sintenisii">
<emphasis id="CE38A076F2956551383F57F19ADE89C8" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Poa sintenisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="06B65FF8F97B2C78D05C7C146C03E930" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa persica" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="0245DCF368B903CB13A1E6F75BCA4FA2" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Poa persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<normalizedToken id="8F49237F2D49CED1A4392BE41CF0C0EC" originalValue="“minor”">
&quot; 
<emphasis id="C387BE4D16EB5846AB8C36359406F8FF" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">minor</emphasis>
&quot;
</normalizedToken>
Boiss. (cited by Mill, in Fl. Turkey 9: 492. 1985) is a nomen nudum since it is a herbarium name on 
<emphasis id="289F661BD01A625BA075F0EDE252A883" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Bourgeau 271</emphasis>
, syntype of var. 
<taxonomicName id="0EB66926B3751925137E8AF5D732E7EE" authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1884" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. alpina" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="persica" variety="alpina">alpina</taxonomicName>
Boiss.; this name is also inscribed on 
<emphasis id="624EB731513A86E714CE460C4DEF45AB" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Kotschy 12d</emphasis>
(p.p. G00308174), but the latter is original material, not a syntype, mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="BB69C7B57E34AC5981C44BBEA08CE3C3" author="Boissier, PE" editor="Boissier, PE" journalOrPublisher="5. H. Georg, Basilae" pageId="20" pageNumber="89" pagination="432 - 692" refId="B3" refString="Boissier, PE, 1884. Ordo CXLI. Gramineae. In: Boissier, PE, Ed., Flora Orientalis, vol. 5. H. Georg, Basilae: 432 - 692" title="Ordo CXLI. Gramineae." volumeTitle="Flora Orientalis, vol." year="1884">Boissier (1884)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
